rComments: do not take this course.
He's great and I loved the class

You can't knock Miall for a boring course. GLG103 is designed for humanities students, not geology students. For science distribution take this course. Miall does his best to make the information interesting and relevant. Reread the sample tests a few times, make some notes in class, and DONT BUY THE BOOK - USELESS, he even says that in class.

The class was dull. Can't blame the professor though, rocks aren't exactly interesting. Tests are not hard if you prepare well. Exam was a joke. Textbook is useless. Course focuses on theory, not issues. Instructor talks too fast. I don't recommend this course. Takes too much time, and almost useless.

tests were all short answer & about things U didnt even think was taught. if U attempted a question but were completely wrong he gave U atleast 1 mark. slides were all pictures no text to study so you had to write down everything he said. easy to understand. answered questions. book is useless DONT BUY IT nothing from book is on the tests & exam.

Class was probably interesting to a degree, I spent most of the time sleeping. Not entirely his fault though. Tests were all short answers and made up of the most unlikely questions. However 1/2 the exam is given in advance; just prepare and memorize two essays coming into the exam and you'll be fine. I went from a B- to an A- by doing that.

Very nice man and taught well. Good introduction to geology. Always willing to answer my questions.

While the material is pretty lame, this prof attempts to make it a somewhat enjoyable experience.  Though not successful all the time, it sure makes rocks more enjoyable.  Can't blame him for not putting in a strong effort.  Great intro to the world of geology.
